Command Piping and Redirection

Determine the Number of Files and Folders in /usr/share
List the current working directory.
pwd
List the contents of the home directory.
ls
List the contents of the /usr/share directory.
ls /usr/share/
Determine the number of files and folders in the /usr/share/ directory.
ls /usr/share/ | wc -l
Rerun the previous command, and send the output to the value.txt file.
ls /usr/share/ | wc -l > ~/value.txt
List the contents of the current working directory.
ls
List the contents of the value.txt file.
cat value.txt
Determine the Number of Unpacked Entries in /var/log/dpkg.log
List all of the unpacked entries in the directory.
cat /var/log/dpkg.log | grep unpacked
Determine the number of unpacked entries in the directory.
cat /var/log/dpkg.log | grep unpacked | wc -l
Rerun the previous command, and send the output to the value.txt file.
cat /var/log/dpkg.log | grep unpacked | wc -l >> value.txt
Verify that this was successful.
cat value.txt
Determine the Total Number of Entries in /var/log/dpkg.log
Run the following command:
cat /var/log/dpkg.log | wc -l
Rerun the previous command, and send the output to the value.txt file.
cat /var/log/dpkg.log | wc -l >> value.txt
Verify that this was successful.
cat value.txt
Conclusion
